{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":0,"text":"There's actually a major health crisis today"},{"time":3000,"text":"in terms of the shortage of organs."},{"time":5000,"text":"The fact is that we're living longer."},{"time":7000,"text":"Medicine has done a much better job"},{"time":9000,"text":"of making us live longer,"},{"time":11000,"text":"and the problem is, as we age,"},{"time":13000,"text":"our organs tend to fail more,"},{"time":16000,"text":"and so currently"},{"time":18000,"text":"there are not enough organs to go around."},{"time":20000,"text":"In fact, in the last 10 years,"},{"time":22000,"text":"the number of patients requiring an organ has doubled,"},{"time":25000,"text":"while in the same time,"},{"time":27000,"text":"the actual number of transplants has barely gone up."},{"time":30000,"text":"So this is now a public health crisis."}]},{"cues":[{"time":32000,"text":"So that's where this field comes in"},{"time":34000,"text":"that we call the field of regenerative medicine."},{"time":36000,"text":"It really involves many different areas."},{"time":38000,"text":"You can use, actually, scaffolds,"},{"time":40000,"text":"biomaterials --"},{"time":42000,"text":"they're like the piece of your blouse or your shirt --"},{"time":44000,"text":"but specific materials you can actually implant in patients"},{"time":47000,"text":"and they will do well and help you regenerate."},{"time":50000,"text":"Or we can use cells alone,"},{"time":53000,"text":"either your very own cells"},{"time":55000,"text":"or different stem cell populations."},{"time":57000,"text":"Or we can use both."},{"time":59000,"text":"We can use, actually, biomaterials"},{"time":61000,"text":"and the cells together."},{"time":63000,"text":"And that's where the field is today."}]},{"cues":[{"time":66000,"text":"But it's actually not a new field."},{"time":68000,"text":"Interestingly, this is a book"},{"time":70000,"text":"that was published back in 1938."},{"time":73000,"text":"It's titled \"The Culture of Organs.\""},{"time":75000,"text":"The first author, Alexis Carrel, a Nobel Prize winner."},{"time":78000,"text":"He actually devised some of the same technologies"},{"time":80000,"text":"used today for suturing blood vessels,"},{"time":82000,"text":"and some of the blood vessel grafts we use today"},{"time":85000,"text":"were actually designed by Alexis."},{"time":88000,"text":"But I want you to note his co-author:"},{"time":91000,"text":"Charles Lindbergh."},{"time":93000,"text":"That's the same Charles Lindbergh"},{"time":96000,"text":"who actually spent the rest of his life"},{"time":98000,"text":"working with Alexis"},{"time":100000,"text":"at the Rockefeller Institute in New York"},{"time":102000,"text":"in the area of the culture of organs."}]},{"cues":[{"time":104000,"text":"So if the field's been around for so long,"},{"time":106000,"text":"why so few clinical advances?"},{"time":108000,"text":"And that really has to do to many different challenges."},{"time":111000,"text":"But if I were to point to three challenges,"},{"time":113000,"text":"the first one is actually the design of materials"},{"time":115000,"text":"that could go in your body"},{"time":117000,"text":"and do well over time."},{"time":119000,"text":"And many advances now,"},{"time":121000,"text":"we can do that fairly readily."},{"time":123000,"text":"The second challenge was cells."},{"time":125000,"text":"We could not get enough of your cells to grow outside of your body."},{"time":128000,"text":"Over the last 20 years, we've basically tackled that."},{"time":131000,"text":"Many scientists can now grow many different types of cells."},{"time":133000,"text":"Plus we have stem cells."},{"time":135000,"text":"But even now, 2011,"},{"time":138000,"text":"there's still certain cells that we just can't grow from the patient."},{"time":142000,"text":"Liver cells, nerve cells, pancreatic cells --"},{"time":145000,"text":"we still can't grow them even today."},{"time":148000,"text":"And the third challenge is vascularity,"},{"time":150000,"text":"the actual supply of blood"},{"time":153000,"text":"to allow those organs or tissues to survive"},{"time":156000,"text":"once we regenerate them."}]},{"cues":[{"time":158000,"text":"So we can actually use biomaterials now."},{"time":160000,"text":"This is actually a biomaterial."},{"time":162000,"text":"We can weave them, knit them, or we can make them like you see here."},{"time":165000,"text":"This is actually like a cotton candy machine."},{"time":168000,"text":"You saw the spray going in."},{"time":170000,"text":"That was like the fibers of the cotton candy"},{"time":172000,"text":"creating this structure, this tubularized structure,"},{"time":174000,"text":"which is a biomaterial"},{"time":176000,"text":"that we can then use"},{"time":178000,"text":"to help your body regenerate"},{"time":180000,"text":"using your very own cells to do so."},{"time":183000,"text":"And that's exactly what we did here."}]},{"cues":[{"time":185000,"text":"This is actually a patient"},{"time":187000,"text":"who [was] presented with a deceased organ,"},{"time":189000,"text":"and we then created one of these smart biomaterials,"},{"time":192000,"text":"and then we then used that smart biomaterial"},{"time":194000,"text":"to replace and repair"},{"time":197000,"text":"that patient's structure."},{"time":199000,"text":"What we did was we actually"},{"time":201000,"text":"used the biomaterial as a bridge"},{"time":203000,"text":"so that the cells in the organ"},{"time":205000,"text":"could walk on that bridge, if you will,"},{"time":207000,"text":"and help to bridge the gap"},{"time":209000,"text":"to regenerate that tissue."},{"time":211000,"text":"And you see that patient now six months after"},{"time":213000,"text":"with an X-ray showing you the regenerated tissue,"},{"time":216000,"text":"which is fully regenerated"},{"time":218000,"text":"when you analyze it under the microscope."},{"time":221000,"text":"We can also use cells alone."},{"time":223000,"text":"These are actually cells that we obtained."},{"time":226000,"text":"These are stem cells that we create from specific sources,"},{"time":229000,"text":"and we can drive them to become heart cells,"},{"time":231000,"text":"and they start beating in culture."},{"time":233000,"text":"So they know what to do."},{"time":235000,"text":"The cells genetically know what to do,"},{"time":237000,"text":"and they start beating together."},{"time":239000,"text":"Now today, many clinical trials"},{"time":241000,"text":"are using different kinds of stem cells"},{"time":243000,"text":"for heart disease."},{"time":245000,"text":"So that's actually now in patients."}]},{"cues":[{"time":248000,"text":"Or if we're going to use larger structures"},{"time":250000,"text":"to replace larger structures,"},{"time":252000,"text":"we can then use the patient's own cells,"},{"time":254000,"text":"or some cell population,"},{"time":256000,"text":"and the biomaterials,"},{"time":258000,"text":"the scaffolds, together."},{"time":260000,"text":"So the concept here:"},{"time":262000,"text":"so if you do have a deceased or injured organ,"},{"time":265000,"text":"we take a very small piece of that tissue,"},{"time":267000,"text":"less than half the size of a postage stamp."},{"time":270000,"text":"We then tease the cells apart,"},{"time":273000,"text":"we grow the cells outside the body."},{"time":275000,"text":"We then take a scaffold, a biomaterial --"},{"time":278000,"text":"again, looks very much like a piece of your blouse or your shirt --"},{"time":281000,"text":"we then shape that material,"},{"time":283000,"text":"and we then use those cells to coat that material"},{"time":286000,"text":"one layer at a time --"},{"time":288000,"text":"very much like baking a layer cake, if you will."},{"time":291000,"text":"We then place it in an oven-like device,"},{"time":293000,"text":"and we're able to create that structure"},{"time":295000,"text":"and bring it out."},{"time":297000,"text":"This is actually a heart valve"},{"time":299000,"text":"that we've engineered,"},{"time":301000,"text":"and you can see here, we have the structure of the heart valve"},{"time":304000,"text":"and we've seeded that with cells,"},{"time":307000,"text":"and then we exercise it."},{"time":309000,"text":"So you see the leaflets opening and closing --"},{"time":311000,"text":"of this heart valve"},{"time":313000,"text":"that's currently being used experimentally"},{"time":317000,"text":"to try to get it to further studies."}]},{"cues":[{"time":320000,"text":"Another technology"},{"time":322000,"text":"that we have used in patients"},{"time":324000,"text":"actually involves bladders."},{"time":326000,"text":"We actually take a very small piece of the bladder from the patient --"},{"time":329000,"text":"less than half the size of a postage stamp."},{"time":332000,"text":"We then grow the cells outside the body,"},{"time":334000,"text":"take the scaffold, coat the scaffold with the cells --"},{"time":336000,"text":"the patient's own cells, two different cell types."},{"time":339000,"text":"We then put it in this oven-like device."},{"time":342000,"text":"It has the same conditions as the human body --"},{"time":344000,"text":"37 degrees centigrade, 95 percent oxygen."},{"time":347000,"text":"A few weeks later, you have your engineered organ"},{"time":350000,"text":"that we're able to implant back into the patient."},{"time":353000,"text":"For these specific patients, we actually just suture these materials."},{"time":356000,"text":"We use three-dimensional imagining analysis,"},{"time":359000,"text":"but we actually created these biomaterials by hand."}]},{"cues":[{"time":363000,"text":"But we now have better ways"},{"time":365000,"text":"to create these structures with the cells."},{"time":367000,"text":"We use now some type of technologies,"},{"time":371000,"text":"where for solid organs, for example,"},{"time":373000,"text":"like the liver,"},{"time":375000,"text":"what we do is we take discard livers."},{"time":378000,"text":"As you know, a lot of organs are actually discarded, not used."},{"time":381000,"text":"So we can take these liver structures,"},{"time":383000,"text":"which are not going to be used,"},{"time":385000,"text":"and we then put them in a washing machine-like structure"},{"time":389000,"text":"that will allow the cells to be washed away."},{"time":391000,"text":"Two weeks later,"},{"time":393000,"text":"you have something that looks like a liver."},{"time":395000,"text":"You can hold it like a liver,"},{"time":397000,"text":"but it has no cells; it's just a skeleton of the liver."},{"time":400000,"text":"And we then can re-perfuse the liver with cells,"},{"time":404000,"text":"preserving the blood vessel tree."},{"time":406000,"text":"So we actually perfuse first the blood vessel tree"},{"time":409000,"text":"with the patient's own blood vessel cells,"},{"time":411000,"text":"and we then infiltrate the parenchyma with the liver cells."},{"time":414000,"text":"And we now have been able just to show"},{"time":416000,"text":"the creation of human liver tissue"},{"time":418000,"text":"just this past month"},{"time":420000,"text":"using this technology."}]},{"cues":[{"time":424000,"text":"Another technology that we've used"},{"time":426000,"text":"is actually that of printing."},{"time":428000,"text":"This is actually a desktop inkjet printer,"},{"time":431000,"text":"but instead of using ink,"},{"time":433000,"text":"we're using cells."},{"time":435000,"text":"And you can actually see here the printhead"},{"time":437000,"text":"going through and printing this structure,"},{"time":439000,"text":"and it takes about 40 minutes to print this structure."},{"time":441000,"text":"And there's a 3D elevator"},{"time":443000,"text":"that then actually goes down one layer at a time"},{"time":445000,"text":"each time the printhead goes through."},{"time":447000,"text":"And then finally you're able to get that structure out."},{"time":450000,"text":"You can pop that structure out of the printer and implant it."},{"time":453000,"text":"And this is actually a piece of bone"},{"time":455000,"text":"that I'm going to show you in this slide"},{"time":458000,"text":"that was actually created with this desktop printer"},{"time":461000,"text":"and implanted as you see here."},{"time":464000,"text":"That was all new bone that was implanted"},{"time":466000,"text":"using these techniques."}]},{"cues":[{"time":469000,"text":"Another more advanced technology we're looking at right now,"},{"time":473000,"text":"our next generation of technologies,"},{"time":475000,"text":"are more sophisticated printers."},{"time":477000,"text":"This particular printer we're designing now"},{"time":480000,"text":"is actually one where we print right on the patient."},{"time":483000,"text":"So what you see here --"},{"time":485000,"text":"I know it sounds funny,"},{"time":487000,"text":"but that's the way it works."},{"time":489000,"text":"Because in reality, what you want to do"},{"time":492000,"text":"is you actually want to have the patient on the bed with the wound,"},{"time":495000,"text":"and you have a scanner,"},{"time":497000,"text":"basically like a flatbed scanner."},{"time":499000,"text":"That's what you see here on the right side."},{"time":501000,"text":"You see a scanner technology"},{"time":503000,"text":"that first scans the wound on the patient"},{"time":506000,"text":"and then it comes back with the printheads"},{"time":509000,"text":"actually printing the layers that you require"},{"time":512000,"text":"on the patients themselves."}]},{"cues":[{"time":514000,"text":"This is how it actually works."},{"time":516000,"text":"Here's the scanner going through,"},{"time":518000,"text":"scanning the wound."},{"time":520000,"text":"Once it's scanned,"},{"time":522000,"text":"it sends information in the correct layers of cells"},{"time":524000,"text":"where they need to be."},{"time":526000,"text":"And now you're going to see here"},{"time":528000,"text":"a demo of this actually being done"},{"time":530000,"text":"in a representative wound."},{"time":533000,"text":"And we actually do this with a gel so that you can lift the gel material."},{"time":536000,"text":"So once those cells are on the patient"},{"time":538000,"text":"they will stick where they need to be."},{"time":540000,"text":"And this is actually new technology"},{"time":542000,"text":"still under development."}]},{"cues":[{"time":545000,"text":"We're also working on more sophisticated printers."},{"time":548000,"text":"Because in reality, our biggest challenge"},{"time":550000,"text":"are the solid organs."},{"time":552000,"text":"I don't know if you realize this,"},{"time":554000,"text":"but 90 percent of the patients on the transplant list"},{"time":558000,"text":"are actually waiting for a kidney."},{"time":561000,"text":"Patients are dying every day"},{"time":563000,"text":"because we don't have enough of those organs to go around."},{"time":566000,"text":"So this is more challenging --"},{"time":568000,"text":"large organ, vascular,"},{"time":570000,"text":"a lot of blood vessel supply,"},{"time":572000,"text":"a lot of cells present."},{"time":574000,"text":"So the strategy here is --"},{"time":576000,"text":"this is actually a CT scan, an X-ray --"},{"time":578000,"text":"and we go layer by layer,"},{"time":580000,"text":"using computerized morphometric imaging analysis"},{"time":582000,"text":"and 3D reconstruction"},{"time":584000,"text":"to get right down to those patient's own kidneys."},{"time":587000,"text":"We then are able to actually image those,"},{"time":590000,"text":"do 360 degree rotation"},{"time":592000,"text":"to analyze the kidney"},{"time":594000,"text":"in its full volumetric characteristics,"},{"time":598000,"text":"and we then are able"},{"time":600000,"text":"to actually take this information"},{"time":602000,"text":"and then scan this"},{"time":604000,"text":"in a printing computerized form."},{"time":606000,"text":"So we go layer by layer through the organ,"},{"time":609000,"text":"analyzing each layer as we go through the organ,"},{"time":612000,"text":"and we then are able to send that information, as you see here,"},{"time":616000,"text":"through the computer"},{"time":618000,"text":"and actually design the organ"},{"time":620000,"text":"for the patient."},{"time":622000,"text":"This actually shows the actual printer."},{"time":625000,"text":"And this actually shows that printing."}]},{"cues":[{"time":627000,"text":"In fact, we actually have the printer right here."},{"time":631000,"text":"So while we've been talking today,"},{"time":634000,"text":"you can actually see the printer"},{"time":637000,"text":"back here in the back stage."},{"time":640000,"text":"That's actually the actual printer right now,"},{"time":642000,"text":"and that's been printing this kidney structure"},{"time":644000,"text":"that you see here."},{"time":646000,"text":"It takes about seven hours to print a kidney,"},{"time":648000,"text":"so this is about three hours into it now."},{"time":651000,"text":"And Dr. Kang's going to walk onstage right now,"},{"time":654000,"text":"and we're actually going to show you one of these kidneys"},{"time":657000,"text":"that we printed a little bit earlier today."},{"time":663000,"text":"Put a pair of gloves here."},{"time":671000,"text":"Thank you."},{"time":673000,"text":"Go backwards."},{"time":681000,"text":"So, these gloves are a little bit small on me, but here it is."},{"time":684000,"text":"You can actually see that kidney"},{"time":686000,"text":"as it was printed earlier today."}]},{"cues":[{"time":688000,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":704000,"text":"Has a little bit of consistency to it."},{"time":708000,"text":"This is Dr. Kang who's been working with us on this project,"},{"time":711000,"text":"and part of our team."},{"time":713000,"text":"Thank you, Dr. Kang. I appreciate it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":716000,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":721000,"text":"So this is actually a new generation."},{"time":723000,"text":"This is actually the printer that you see here onstage."},{"time":725000,"text":"And this is actually a new technology we're working on now."},{"time":729000,"text":"In reality, we now have a long history of doing this."},{"time":733000,"text":"I'm going to share with you a clip"},{"time":735000,"text":"in terms of technology we have had in patients now for a while."}]},{"cues":[{"time":738000,"text":"And this is actually a very brief clip --"},{"time":740000,"text":"only about 30 seconds --"},{"time":742000,"text":"of a patient who actually received an organ."}]},{"cues":[{"time":745000,"text":"(Video) Luke Massella: I was really sick. I could barely get out of bed."},{"time":747000,"text":"I was missing school. It was pretty much miserable."},{"time":750000,"text":"I couldn't go out"},{"time":752000,"text":"and play basketball at recess"},{"time":754000,"text":"without feeling like I was going to pass out"},{"time":756000,"text":"when I got back inside."},{"time":758000,"text":"I felt so sick."},{"time":761000,"text":"I was facing basically a lifetime of dialysis,"},{"time":764000,"text":"and I don't even like to think about what my life would be like"},{"time":766000,"text":"if I was on that."},{"time":768000,"text":"So after the surgery,"},{"time":770000,"text":"life got a lot better for me."},{"time":772000,"text":"I was able to do more things."},{"time":774000,"text":"I was able to wrestle in high school."},{"time":776000,"text":"I became the captain of the team, and that was great."},{"time":779000,"text":"I was able to be a normal kid with my friends."},{"time":782000,"text":"And because they used my own cells to build this bladder,"},{"time":785000,"text":"it's going to be with me."},{"time":787000,"text":"I've got it for life, so I'm all set."}]},{"cues":[{"time":790000,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":828000,"text":"Juan Enriquez: These experiments sometimes work,"},{"time":830000,"text":"and it's very cool when they do."},{"time":832000,"text":"Luke, come up please."}]},{"cues":[{"time":839000,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":854000,"text":"So Luke, before last night,"},{"time":856000,"text":"when's the last time you saw Tony?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":858000,"text":"LM: Ten years ago, when I had my surgery --"},{"time":861000,"text":"and it's really great to see him."}]},{"cues":[{"time":863000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":865000,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":871000,"text":"JE: And tell us a little bit about what you're doing."}]},{"cues":[{"time":873000,"text":"LM: Well right now I'm in college at the University of Connecticut."},{"time":876000,"text":"I'm a sophomore and studying communications, TV and mass media,"},{"time":880000,"text":"and basically trying to live life like a normal kid,"},{"time":883000,"text":"which I always wanted growing up."},{"time":885000,"text":"But it was hard to do that when I was born with spina bifida"},{"time":887000,"text":"and my kidneys and bladder weren't working."},{"time":890000,"text":"I went through about 16 surgeries,"},{"time":892000,"text":"and it seemed impossible to do that"},{"time":894000,"text":"when I was in kidney failure when I was 10."},{"time":897000,"text":"And this surgery came along"},{"time":899000,"text":"and basically made me who I am today"},{"time":901000,"text":"and saved my life."}]},{"cues":[{"time":903000,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":914000,"text":"JE: And Tony's done hundreds of these?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":917000,"text":"LM: What I know from, he's working really hard in his lab"},{"time":920000,"text":"and coming up with crazy stuff."},{"time":922000,"text":"I know I was one of the first 10 people to have this surgery."},{"time":925000,"text":"And when I was 10, I didn't realize how amazing it was."},{"time":928000,"text":"I was a little kid, and I was like,"},{"time":930000,"text":"\"Yeah. I'll have that. I'll have that surgery.\""},{"time":932000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":934000,"text":"All I wanted to do was to get better,"},{"time":936000,"text":"and I didn't realize how amazing it really was until now that I'm older"},{"time":939000,"text":"and I see the amazing things that he's doing."}]},{"cues":[{"time":943000,"text":"JE: When you got this call out of the blue --"},{"time":946000,"text":"Tony's really shy,"},{"time":948000,"text":"and it took a lot of convincing"},{"time":950000,"text":"to get somebody as modest as Tony"},{"time":952000,"text":"to allow us to bring Luke."},{"time":955000,"text":"So Luke, you go to your communications professors --"},{"time":957000,"text":"you're majoring in communications --"},{"time":959000,"text":"and you ask them for permission to come to TED,"},{"time":961000,"text":"which might have a little bit to do with communications,"},{"time":963000,"text":"and what was their reaction?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":966000,"text":"LM: Most of my professors were all for it,"},{"time":968000,"text":"and they said, \"Bring pictures"},{"time":971000,"text":"and show me the clips online,\" and \"I'm happy for you.\""},{"time":974000,"text":"There were a couple that were a little stubborn,"},{"time":976000,"text":"but I had to talk to them."},{"time":978000,"text":"I pulled them aside."}]},{"cues":[{"time":981000,"text":"JE: Well, it's an honor and a privilege to meet you."},{"time":983000,"text":"Thank you so much. (LM: Thank you so much.)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":988000,"text":"JE: Thank you, Tony."}]},{"cues":[{"time":990000,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}